        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the rub plate so it is:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Centered vertically on the rearward tab on the rear reinforcement (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f9609012">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f9609012" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9609012.webp" type="webp" resolution="150"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Even with or slightly forward from the rear edge of the hood.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Pressed firmly against the side of the hood.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grind the tab area of the rear enforcement to provide a composite thickness of .350 inch
                    max. including the outer panel, adhesive and rear reinforcement (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9609013">Figure 3</hotlnk>). Check the composite thickness with a gauge to 1.5 inch
                    depth. This will allow the complete thickness with the .040 inch plate of .390 inch.(Previous
                    specification was .400 inch thickness at the rear edge).
                </para>
                <figure id="f9609013" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9609013.webp" type="webp" resolution="150"/>
                    <caption>Figure 3.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a C clamp or vise grips to firmly clamp the rub plate against the side of the hood
                    while protecting the painted surface of the hood. Position the clamp to allow working space for the
                    rivet tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While the plate is clamped in place, use the holes in the plate as a template to drill
                    two rivet holes in the hood. Use the holes adjacent to the flat area of the reinforcement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the rub plate to the hood reinforcement with two 1/4 inch KT Cherry Rivets.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clamp.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat this procedure on the opposite side of the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
